Ghoul: Currently this is an umbrella term for 4 roles that a host can put into their setup (Hungry Ghoul - Starts on N1 with a kill power; Perceptive Ghoul - Starts with a check power; Cunning Ghoul - Starts with a stalk power; Regular Ghoul - Starts with no power). Ghoul is able to ‚Äúfeed‚Äù on a dead body and gain either a kill, check or stalk power. Until the Ghoul uses this power,, they cannot ‚Äúfeed‚Äù on another dead body. If the ghoul feeds on a fellow undead member who‚Äôs in GY, the Ghoul assumes that exact role for the rest of the game.  VD: Refer to H2P, there are no changes implemented on this role.  Necromancer: Refer to H2P as well. Only tweak to this role is that a necromancer is seen as a WC user.  Medium: No changes. Refer to H2P.  Banshee: Banshee is a role that activates it‚Äôs power upon being killed (the way a banshee dies doesn‚Äôt affect the activation itself, but it affects when the power can be used). After the banshee dies, they are able to possess any living player the morning after their death. Every night, the banshee returns to the GY and is able to possess any other player the next morning. This continues for the length of the game. Banshee is also seen as a WC user.

So, the standard BH code that I've followed before goes something like this:
Use the H2P list of roles as a reference point.
The number of minutes indicates the the role in the H2P. Since there are only 28 village roles, this number can be within the first 30 minutes, or the next half.
Example: A message typed at either "xx:01" or "xx:31" indicate that I found a "Beholder".
Now, in the case of 3 factions (or more), the code is altered to have the message indicating the faction.
So in that case, I'll have specific messages that I mention here.
An example: If I found a coven role, I'll talk about politics in my first message, then the time that message was sent will correspond the H2P list of coven roles.

That should cover the basics of the BH code I'm familiar with. I'll suggest that the others ghouls follow this format. Or if you guys have other formats to use, please mention them and we can work out our information exchange during the day.
Now, as for my code, it'll be exactly this version.
Part 1 (faction representation):
If I find a vampire, my first message will be related to horror games.
If I find a village role, my first message will be about the theme used in this game.
If I find a wolf role, the message will be about food.
If I find a coven, my message will be about undeads meta.
Part 2 (exact role):
As mentioned before, the minutes of my first message will be indicative of the role. However, the minutes will be offset by +1.
Example: If I find a beholder, my message will be sent at "xx:02" or "xx:32".
That should settle my ghoul check for tomorrow.
Checking Rarity for the night.
All other ghouls, please mention your checks before signing off so we make sure there is no cross-checking.
